|align="center" colspan="13" style="font-size: 8pt"| "&mdash;" denotes singles that were released but did not chart, or singles not released in a particular territory
|}

<div class="references-small">
;Notes
*A <span id="endnote_A" />[[#ref_A|'''^''']] The non-fade-out version of "Dreaming of Me" appears on the CD versions of ''Speak & Spell'', despite being officially a non-album track.
*B <span id="endnote_B" />[[#ref_B|'''^''']] "But Not Tonight" was released as the A-side only in the United States.
*C <span id="endnote_C" />[[#ref_C|'''^''']] In the United States, Australia and [[New Zealand]] the [[megamix]] of "Route 66" and "Behind the Wheel" are the songs that charted.
*D <span id="endnote_D" />[[#ref_D|'''^''']] "Dangerous" and "Halo" were not released as singles. They only charted on the Modern Rock Tracks chart, because it measures airplay on alternative rock radio stations in the United States. 
*E <span id="endnote_E" />[[#ref_E|'''^''']] "Home" was released as a [[double A-side]] with "Useless" in the United States.
*F <span id="endnote_F" />[[#ref_F|'''^''']] "Goodnight Lovers" was not eligible to chart in the United Kingdom because its single release contained more than three tracks
*G <span id="endnote_G" />[[#ref_G|'''^''']] "Remixes 04" were limited edition 12" releases of remixes released to complement the release of "Enjoy the Silence '04".  
</div>

==Box sets==
{| class="wikitable"
!Year
!Notes
|-
|rowspan="5"|1991
|''Singles Box, Vol. 1''
* Released on [[November 28]] [[1991]]
* Labels: [[Rhino Entertainment|Rhino]], [[Warner Music Group|WEA]]
* Includes "Dreaming of Me", "New Life", "Just Can't Get Enough", "See You", "The Meaning of Life" and "Leave in Silence".
* Notes: Re-released in 2004.
|-
|''X1''
* Released in 1991
* Labels: WEA
* Notes: Released only in [[Japan]].
|-
|''X2''
* Released in 1991
* Labels: WEA
* Notes: Released only in Japan.
|-
|''Singles Box, Vol. 2''
* Released on November 28, 1991
* Labels: Rhino, WEA
* Includes "Get the Balance Right!", "Everything Counts", "Love in Itself", "People Are People", "Master and Servant" and "Blasphemous Rumours".
* Notes: Re-released in 2004.
|-
|''Singles Box, Vol. 3''
* Released on [[December 12]] [[1991]]
* Labels: Rhino, WEA
* Includes "Shake the Disease", "It's Called a Heart", "Stripped", "A Question of Lust", "A Question of Time" and "Little 15".
* Notes: Re-released in 2004.
|-
|rowspan="3"|2004
|''Singles Box, Vol. 4''
* Released on [[March 30]], [[2004]]
* Labels: Rhino, WEA
* Includes "Strangelove", "Never Let Me Down Again", "Behind the Wheel", "Everything Counts (Live)", "Personal Jesus" and "Enjoy the Silence".
|-
|''Singles Box, Vol. 5''
* Released on March 30, 2004
* Labels: Rhino, WEA
* Includes "Policy of Truth", "World in My Eyes", "I Feel You", "Walking in My Shoes", "Condemnation" and "In Your Room".
|-
|''Singles Box, Vol. 6''
* Released on March 30, 2004
* Labels: Rhino, WEA
* Includes "Barrel of Gun", "It's No Good", "Home", "Useless", "Only When I Lose Myself" and "Dream On".
|-
|}

==B-sides==

{|class="wikitable"
! Year
! Song
! A-side
! Comments
|-
|rowspan="3"| 1981<sup><span id="ref_H" />[[#endnote_H|'''[H]''']]</sup>
| "Ice Machine"
| "[[Dreaming of Me]]"
| Appears as a bonus track on CD and remastered DVD versions of ''[[Speak & Spell (album)|Speak & Spell]]''. 
|-
| "Shout"
| "[[New Life]]"
| Appears as a bonus track on CD and remastered DVD versions of ''Speak & Spell''. "Rio Mix" appeared on the compilation ''[[Remixes 81 - 04]]''. 
|-
| "Any Second Now"
| "[[Just Can't Get Enough]]"
| Appears as a bonus track on CD and remastered DVD versions of ''Speak & Spell''. This is an instrumental. "Any Second Now (Voices)", sung by Martin Gore, is the actual album version. 
|-
|Rowspan="3"|1982
| "Now, This Is Fun"
| [[See You]]
| Appears on the remastered DVD of ''[[A Broken Frame]]''.
|-
| "Oberkorn (It's A Small Town)"
| "[[The Meaning Of Love]]"
| Appears on the remastered DVD of ''A Broken Frame''. Instrumental.
|-
| "Excerpts From: My Secret Garden"
| "[[Leave In Silence]]"
| Instrumental version of "My Secret Garden" which appears on ''A Broken Frame''. "Excerpts From" version also appears on the remastered DVD of the album. "Further Excerpts From: My Secret Garden" is a longer mix appearing on the 12" and CD singles.
|-
|Rowspan="3"|1983
| "The Great Outdoors!"
| "[[Get the Balance Right!]]"
| First songwriting credit for Alan Wilder, jointly with Martin Gore. Appears on the remastered DVD of ''[[Construction Time Again]]'', along with the A-side.
|-
| "Work Hard"
| "[[Everything Counts]]"
| Credited to Gore and Wilder. Appears on the remastered DVD of ''Construction Time Again''. 
|-
| "Fools"
| "[[Love, In Itself]]"
| Written by Wilder. Appears on the remastered DVD of ''Construction Time Again''. "Fools (Bigger)" appears on the 12" and CD singles.
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1984<sup><span id="ref_I" />[[#endnote_I|'''[I]''']]</sup>
| "In Your Memory"
| "[[People Are People]]"
| Written by Wilder. Appears on the remastered DVD of ''[[Some Great Reward]]''.
|-
| "(Set Me Free) Remotivate Me"
| "[[Master and Servant]]"
| Appears on the remastered DVD of ''Some Great Reward''.
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1985
| "Flexible"
| "[[Shake The Disease]]"
| Appears on the US-only compilation ''[[Catching Up With Depeche Mode]]''. Also appears on the remastered DVD of ''[[Black Celebration]]''.
|-
| "Fly On The Windscreen"
| "[[It's Called a Heart]]"
| So-called "Final" version was an official track on ''Black Celebration'' released a year later. Single version also appears on the US-only compilation ''Catching Up With Depeche Mode'', as well as being bonus track on the remastered DVD of ''Black Celebration''. 
|-
|Rowspan="4"|1986<sup><span id="ref_J" />[[#endnote_J|'''[J]''']]</sup>
| "But Not Tonight"
|Rowspan="3"| "[[Stripped (song)|Stripped]]"
|Rowspan="3"| In the US only "But Not Tonight" was released as the A-side, with "Stripped" as the B-side. Also made an appearance on the ''[[Modern Girls]]'' soundtrack. "Black Day", sung by Martin Gore, and credited to Gore, Wilder and Daniel Miller, is an acoustic version of "Black Celebration", the title track of the album, whilst "Breathing in Fumes" uses samples from "Stripped". Included on CD single and the CD and remastered DVD versions of ''Black Celebration''.
|-
| "Black Day"
|-
| "Breathing in Fumes"
|-
| "Christmas Island"
| "[[A Question of Lust]]"
| Written by Gore and Wilder, instrumental. Included on the remastered DVD of ''Black Celebration''. 
|-
|Rowspan="5"|1987
| "Pimpf" and "Fpmip"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[Strangelove]]"
|Rowspan="2"| "Pimpf", an album track, is an instrumental and the 7" B-side, with another version, "Fpmip", appearing on 12" and CD (the latter also including the original). "Agent Orange", another instrumental, is the 12" B-side, also appearing on CD. It was included on the CD and remastered DVD versions of ''[[Music For The Masses]]''.
|-
| "Agent Orange"
|-
| "Pleasure, Little Treasure"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[Never Let Me Down Again]]" 
|Rowspan="2"| "Pleasure, Little Treasure" was the 7" B-side and also appears on CD. The "Glitter Mix" of this track was included on the CD and remastered DVD versions of ''Music For The Masses''. "To Have And To Hold" is an album track, but the "Spanish Taster" is a short acoustic version. This was the 12" B-side and also appears on CD, as well as the CD and remastered DVD versions of the album.
|-
| "To Have And To Hold (Spanish Taster)"
|-
| "[[Route 66 (song)|Route 66]]"
| "[[Behind the Wheel]]"
| Cover version of the [[Bobby Troup]] song "(Get Your Kicks On) Route 66". Appears on the remastered DVD of ''Music For The Masses''.
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1988<sup><span id="ref_K" />[[#endnote_K|'''[K]''']]</sup>
| "Stjarna"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[Little 15]]"
|Rowspan="2"| The 7" B-side "Stjarna" is an instrumental. "Moonlight Sonata No. 14" is the 12" B-side and is a recording of an impromptu performance by Alan Wilder of [[Beethoven's]] piano sonata No. 14, popularly known as the "Moonlight Sonata". Both tracks appear on CD single and the remastered DVD of ''Music For The Masses''.
|-
|"[[Piano Sonata No. 14 (Beethoven)|Moonlight Sonata No. 14]]"
|-
| 1989<sup><span id="ref_L" />[[#endnote_L|'''[L]''']]</sup>
| "Dangerous"
| "[[Personal Jesus]]"
| Never released as a single, but charted on the US Modern Rock Tracks chart, which measures airplay on alternative rock radio stations in the United States. Makes an appearance on the US CD Maxi-single and the remastered DVD version of ''[[Violator]]''.
|-
|Rowspan="5"|1990
| "Memphisto"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[Enjoy The Silence]]"
|Rowspan="2"| Both instrumentals, with "Memphisto" on the 7" and "Sibeling" on the 12". Both tracks appear on the US CD maxi-single and the remastered DVD version of ''Violator''.
|-
| "Sibeling"
|-
| "Kaleid"
| "[[Policy of Truth]]"
| Instrumental, appears on the remastered DVD version of ''Violator''.
|-
| "Happiest Girl"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[World In My Eyes]]"
|Rowspan="2"| "Happiest Girl" is the 7" B-side, and "Sea of Sin" is the 12". Both tracks appear on the US CD maxi-single and remastered DVD version of ''Violator''.
|-
| "Sea of Sin"
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1993<sup><span id="ref_M" />[[#endnote_M|'''[M]''']],<span id="ref_N" />[[#endnote_N|'''[N]''']]</sup>
| "My Joy"
| "[[Walking In My Shoes]]"
| The only all-new B-side for the ''[[Songs of Faith and Devotion]]'' singles. Excluded from the album in 1993, but makes an appearance on the remastered DVD. 
|-
| "Death's Door (Jazz Mix)"
| "[[Condemnation (song)|Condemnation]]"
| Remix of the track from the 1991 soundtrack to ''[[Until the End of the World]]'', and therefore its first appearance on a Depeche Mode record. Also appears on the remastered DVD of ''Songs of Faith and Devotion''. 
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1997<sup><span id="ref_O" />[[#endnote_O|'''[O]''']]</sup>
| "Painkiller"
| "[[Barrel of a Gun]]"
| Instrumental. Short version appears on the ''[[Ultra]]'' album as the unlisted track "Junior Painkiller", immediately after "Insight". Single version is a bonus track on the remastered DVD version of the album. 
|-
| "Slowblow"
| "[[It's No Good]]"
| Instrumental. Appears on the remastered DVD of ''Ultra''. 
|-
|Rowspan="2"|1998
| "Surrender"
|Rowspan="2"| "[[Only When I Lose Myself]]"
|Rowspan="2"| "Headstar" is an instrumental. Both appear as bonus tracks on the remastered DVD version of ''Ultra'', along with the A-side, despite the A-side being released on ''[[The Singles (86-98)|The Singles 86>98]]''.
|-
| "Headstar"
|-
|Rowspan="3"|2001<sup><span id="ref_P" />[[#endnote_P|'''[P]''']]</sup>
| "Easy Tiger"
| "[[Dream On]]"
| Instrumental. Also appears as a track on ''[[Exciter]]'', but this album version is heavily edited. The single version appears as a bonus track on the remastered DVD of the album.
|-
| "Dirt"
| "[[I Feel Loved]]"
| A cover of the song by [[Iggy Pop]]. Also appears on the ''[[Resident Evil]]'' soundtrack, as well as the remastered DVD of ''Exciter''.
|-
| "Zenstation"
| "[[Freelove]]"
| Instrumental. appears as a bonus track on the remastered DVD of ''Exciter''. 
|-
|Rowspan="2"|2005
| "Free"
| "[[Precious (song)|Precious]]"
| Bonus track on the Japanese release of ''[[Playing The Angel]]'', but "Bare" version appears in the Electronic Press Kit (EPK).
|-
| "Newborn"
| "[[A Pain That I'm Used To]]"
| Only available on the single or as download.
|-
| 2006<sup><span id="ref_Q" />[[#endnote_Q|'''[Q]''']],<span id="ref_R" />[[#endnote_R|'''[R]''']]</sup>
| "Better Days"
| "[[Suffer Well]]"
| Only available on the single or as download. 
|}

<div class="references-small">
;Notes
*H <span id="endnote_H" />[[#ref_H|'''^''']] In the US, "Tora Tora Tora" was the B-side to "Just Can't Get Enough".
*I <span id="endnote_I" />[[#ref_I|'''^''']] The final ''Some Great Reward'' single, "Blasphemous Rumours"/"Somebody", was a double A-side.
*J <span id="endnote_J" />[[#ref_J|'''^''']] The third single from ''Black Celebration'', "A Question of Time" was backed by a live version of the album's title track, namely "Black Celebration".
*K <span id="endnote_K" />[[#ref_K|'''^''']] The US-only "Strangelove '88" was backed by a remix of the album track "Nothing".
*L <span id="endnote_L" />[[#ref_L|'''^''']] "Everything Counts (Live)" released earlier that year was backed by a live version of "Nothing".
*M <span id="endnote_M" />[[#ref_M|'''^''']] The first single from ''Songs of Faith and Devotion'', "I Feel You", was backed by "One Caress", an album track.
*N <span id="endnote_N" />[[#ref_N|'''^''']] The fourth single from ''Songs of Faith and Devotion'', 1994's "In Your Room", was backed by the   "Adrenaline Mix" of the album track "Higher Love".
*O <span id="endnote_O" />[[#ref_O|'''^''']] The other ''Ultra'' singles, "Home" and "Useless", had no official B-sides, with live tracks and remixes backing the single versions of these tracks. They were released as a double A-side in the US.
*P <span id="endnote_P" />[[#ref_P|'''^''']] The fourth single from ''Exciter'', 2002's "Goodnight Lovers", was backed by remixes of the album tracks "When The Body Speaks" and "The Dead Of Night".
*Q <span id="endnote_Q" />[[#ref_Q|'''^''']] The final ''Playing the Angel'' single, "John the Revelator"/"Lilian", was a double A-side.
*R <span id="endnote_R" />[[#ref_R|'''^''']] The single "Martyr", from the compilation ''The Best of, Vol. 1'', had no official B-side, and was backed by remixes.
</div>

