| 1981
| "Photographic"
|''[[Some Bizzare Album]]''
| Various
|
* Compilation released in 1981 by [[Stevo Pearce|Stevo's]] label [[Some Bizzare]]
* Label: Some Bizzare
* Formats: CD, vinyl
* Track contributed: "Photographic", a version different from that on [[Speak & Spell (album)|''Speak & Spell'']]. This track also makes an appearance on the re-released CD version of ''[[The Singles 81-85]]''.
|
|-
| 1986
| "But Not Tonight"
|''[[Modern Girls (soundtrack)]]''
| Various
|
* Soundtrack album for the film ''[[Modern Girls]]'' directed by Jerry Kramer, released in 1986
* Label: [[Warner Bros. Records]]
* Format: vinyl, cassette
* Track contributed: "[[But Not Tonight]]", released as a single in the US, but as the B-side to "[[Stripped]]" in Europe.
|
|-
| 1991
| "Death's Door"
|''[[Until the End of the World (soundtrack)]]''
| Various
|
* Soundtrack album for the film ''[[Until the End of the World]]'' directed by [[Wim Wenders]], released in 1991.
* Label: Warner Bros. Records
* Format: CD
* Track contributed: "Death's Door", with Martin Gore on lead vocals. "Jazz Mix" of this track later appeared as the B-side to "[[Condemnation (song)|Condemnation]]" in 1993.
| US Billboard (early 1992): 114<ref name="AMG"/>
|-
| 2002
| "Dirt"
|''[[Resident Evil (soundtrack)]]''
| Various
|
* Soundtrack album for the film ''[[Resident Evil (film)|Resident Evil]]'' directed by [[Paul W.S. Anderson]], released in 2002
* Label: [[Roadrunner Records]]
* Format: CD
* Track contributed: "Dirt" (a [[cover]] of an original song by [[Iggy Pop]]). This track appeared as the B-side to "I Feel Loved" released in 2001
|
|}

